Android TV boxes can be a great addition to your home entertainment system, especially if you have a fast broadband connection. It is important to choose the right device, however, as many of these set-top boxes may not support all the software you expect. Many Android media boxes available in South Africa are not Google-certified, meaning that they cannot support certain applications. While you will be able to watch YouTube and Twitch on these uncertified boxes, you will not be able to access services like DStv Now and Netflix. For this reason, it is important to buy a Google-certified Android TV box – especially if you plan to watch content on South Africa’s most popular streaming platforms. Google-certified devices offer support for all official apps as well as official versions of the Android TV OS. Many Google-certified set-top boxes feature similar hardware, as this certification is based largely on the chipset included in the product. For this reason, the Google-certified devices we have compared use the Amlogic S905X or S905X2 chipsets. These chips allow for 4K video support at 60 frames per second and support HDR playback. We have listed some of the best Google-certified Android TV boxes available in South Africa below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-313411" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Ematic-4K-TV-Box.jpg" alt="Ematic 4K TV Box" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Ematic-4K-TV-Box.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Ematic-4K-TV-Box-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Ematic-4K-TV-Box-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-286692" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/xiaomi-mi-s-4k-android-media-streaming-tv-box-mi-tv-box-